Variables : a symbolic name for a chunk of memory to which we can assign values, read manipulate and its contents


**It is possible to have bash show you what it is doing when you run your script. To do this, add a "-x" to the first line of your script, like this:

#!/bin/bash -x
  

case word in
    patterns ) commands ;;
esac
            


